{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"c3518b44-2258-4429-af27-c970ea29831c","content":"Found **1 untestable static** in your project:\n\n| File | Line | Call |\n|------|------|------|\n| `views.py` | 3 | `datetime.now()` |\n\n**Why it's a problem:** `datetime.now()` is a hard-coded static call that can't be mocked easily in tests — you can't freeze or inject time without patching.\n\n**Recommended fix:** Use Django's timezone-aware `django.utils.timezone.now()` (which is easier to mock), or inject a clock dependency. For example:\n\n```python\nfrom django.utils import timezone\n\ndef index(request):\n    now = timezone.now()\n    return render(request, 'index.html', {'time': now})\n```\n\nYou can then freeze time in tests with libraries like `freezegun` or `time-machine`, or mock `django.utils.timezone.now` directly.\n\nThis is a small project with only one occurrence — easy fix!","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"d8648d97-ddfb-4c3c-b636-1b02bfde18ed","outputTokens":221,"requestId":"481E:99ACC:38C155F:3E34B65:69FBFEA5"},"id":"c95e3784-424a-44b2-80fd-164b4397b04c","timestamp":"2026-05-07T02:53:32.240Z","parentId":"16cb6ef9-7c87-4d5c-88fd-d401a58dd272"}
